> If you're looking for a filling and familiar meal to warm you up on these cold
> winter evenings, then a big bowl of pasta is always a winner. This particular
> pasta dish features linguine—spaghetti's slightly flatter friend—along with a
> creamy tomato sauce and perfectly cooked prawns.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @dried linguine{180%grams}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Roughly tear the @fresh basil{10%grams}(roughly torn).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated or use a garlic press).

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

When the pot of water is boiling, add the linguine and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @prawns{180%grams}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and transfer the prawns to a #plate{} or #bowl{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The
> prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Return the (now empty) pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the onion and a pinch of salt and pepper to the pan. Fry until softened,
stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and half the @italian herbs{1/2%sachet} and fry for another minute.

Pour in the @passata{1%pack} and @water{100%ml} and simmer for ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add half the torn basil and half the @creme fraiche{125%grams} to the pan.

Stir in the prawns and cooked pasta and allow to warm through.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Divide between #bowls{} and top with @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams},
remaining torn basil and a dollop of creme fraiche.

Finish off with a sprinkling of @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} to taste.